  "prompt": "What does add on item on Amazon mean?",
  "response": "On Amazon, an \"Add-on Item\" is a product that Amazon sells at a low price, but **only when purchased as part of a larger order.**\n\nHere's a breakdown of what that means:\n\n*   **Low Price:** These items are typically inexpensive, like small toiletries, cleaning supplies, or office accessories. Amazon offers them at a low price point to attract customers.\n*   **Part of a Larger Order:** You can't buy an Add-on Item by itself. Amazon requires you to purchase at least $25 of other eligible items (or meet a similar order value threshold, which may vary) in the same order to include the Add-on Item.\n*   **Shipping Savings:** The Add-on Item program helps Amazon save on shipping costs. By bundling these low-cost items with larger orders, they reduce the number of individual packages they need to ship.\n\n**In summary, think of Add-on Items as bonus deals you can get when you're already buying other things on Amazon.**",
